about.summary: Utilities to support spatial data manipulation, query, sampling and modelling. Functions include models for species population density, download utilities for climate and global deforestation spatial products, spatial smoothing, multivariate separability, point process model for creating pseudo- absences and sub-sampling, polygon and point-distance landscape metrics, auto-logistic model, sampling models, cluster optimization, statistical exploratory tools and raster-based metrics.

name: r-spatialeco
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.2-1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-spatialeco
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/spatialEco_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/spatialEco/spatialEco_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d29e8bb81226b0aa46c3685e37b6a168d46bd5068e4b68d4e1658aea4f56718b

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-envstats
    - r-mass
    - r-rann
    - r-rcurl
    - r-sdmtools
    - r-spatialpack >=0.3
    - r-cluster
    - r-dplyr
    - r-fasterize
    - r-maptools
    - r-raster
    - r-readr
    - r-rgeos
    - r-rms
    - r-sf
    - r-sp
    - r-spatstat
    - r-spdep
    - r-yaimpute
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-envstats
    - r-mass
    - r-rann
    - r-rcurl
    - r-sdmtools
    - r-spatialpack >=0.3
    - r-cluster
    - r-dplyr
    - r-fasterize
    - r-maptools
    - r-raster
    - r-readr
    - r-rgeos
    - r-rms
    - r-sf
    - r-sp
    - r-spatstat
    - r-spdep
    - r-yaimpute

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('spatialEco')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('spatialEco')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/jeffreyevans/spatialEco
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Utilities to support spatial data manipulation, query, sampling and modelling. Functions
    include models for species population density, download utilities for climate and
    global deforestation spatial products, spatial smoothing, multivariate separability,
    point process model for creating pseudo- absences and sub-sampling, polygon and
    point-distance landscape metrics, auto-logistic model, sampling models, cluster
    optimization, statistical exploratory tools and raster-based metrics.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - xhochy
